M194_Read_Write_Param_Response.comment:
To write a parameter use message 0x0C1 with byte #2 set to 1 (write). 
To read a parameter use message 0x0C1 with byte #2 to set 0 (read).

M193_Read_Write_Param_Command.comment:
To write a parameter use message 0x0C1 with byte #2 set to 1 (write). 
To read a parameter use message 0x0C1 with byte #2 to set 0 (read).

M192_Command_Message.comment: The command message is used to transmit data to the controller. This message is sent from a user supplied external controller to the PMxxx controller.

signals.name: D1_Modulation_Index
signals.comment: This is the modulation index. The scale factor is x100. To get the actual modulation index divide the value by 100.

signals.name: D2_Flux_Weakening_Output
signals.comment: This is the current output of the flux regulator.

signals.name: D3_Power_On_Timer
signals.comment: Updated every 3 msec. This will roll over in approximately 150 days!

signals.name: D1_Parameter_Address_Response
signals.comment: Valid EEPROM Parameter CAN addresses are between 100 and 499.

signals.name: D3_Data_Response
signals.comment: All EEPROM data is 16 bits and is contained in bytes 4 and 5. Bytes 6 and 7 should be ignored.

signals.name: D1_Parameter_Address_Command
signals.comment: Valid EEPROM Parameter CAN addresses are between 100 and 499.

signals.name: D3_Data_Command
signals.comment: All EEPROM data is 16 bits and is contained in bytes 4 and 5.

signals.name: Torque_Command
signals.comment: Torque command when in torque mode

signals.name: Speed_Command
signals.comment: Speed commandused when in speed mode

signals.name: Direction_Command
signals.comment: 0=CW, 1=CCW as veiwed from the shaft end of the motor

choices.1: Discharge Enable (if EEPROM parameter is set)

signals.name: Speed_Mode_Enable
signals.comment: 0 = No change to mode, 1 = change to speed mode from torque mode

signals.name: Torque_Limit_Command
signals.comment: Torque Limit, set to 0 to keep default

signals.name: D1_Post_Fault_Lo
signals.comment: Each bit represents a fault. Please refer to PM100 Users Manual for details.

signals.name: D2_Post_Fault_Hi
signals.comment: Each bit represents a fault. Please refer to PM100 Users Manual for details.

signals.name: D3_Run_Fault_Lo
signals.comment: Each bit represents a fault. Please refer to PM100 Users Manual for details.

signals.name: D4_Run_Fault_Hi
signals.comment: Each bit represents a fault. Please refer to PM100 Users Manual for details.

signals.name: D1_VSM_State
signals.comment: Different states for the vehicle state machine

choices.14: Shutdown state for Key Switch Mode 1

signals.name: D2_Inverter_State
signals.comment: Different states for the inverter state machine

signals.name: D4_Inverter_Discharge_State
signals.comment: 0 = Disabled, 1 = Enabled, 2 = Speed Check, 3 = Active, 4 = Complete

signals.name: D7_Direction_Command
signals.comment:
1 = Forward
0 = 'Reverse' if inverter enabled  & 'Stopped' if inverter is disabled

signals.name: D1_DC_Bus_Voltage
signals.comment: The actual measured value of the DC bus voltage

signals.name: D2_Output_Voltage
signals.comment: The calculated value of the output voltage, in peak line-neutral volts

signals.name: D3_VAB_Vd_Voltage
signals.comment: Measured value of the voltage betwen phase A and Phase B

signals.name: D4_VBC_Vq_Voltage
signals.comment: Measured value of the voltage between Phase B and Phase C

signals.name: D1_Phase_A_Current
signals.comment: The measured value of Phase A current

signals.name: D2_Phase_B_Current
signals.comment: The measured value of Phase B current

signals.name: D3_Phase_C_Current
signals.comment: The measured value of Phase C current

signals.name: D1_Motor_Angle_Electrical
signals.comment: The Electrical Angle of the motor as read by the encoder or resolver

signals.name: D2_Motor_Speed
signals.comment: The measured speed of the motor

signals.name: D3_Electrical_Output_Frequency
signals.comment: The actual electrical frequency of the inverter

signals.name: D4_Delta_Resolver_Filtered
signals.comment: Used in calibration of resolver angle adjustment.
